---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title={`About — ${SITE_TITLE}`}
      description="Yarova is an IT placement consultancy built and run by Rohith Yadla — Solutions Architect with 10 years of production consulting experience."
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main>
      <article class="about">
        <div class="about-inner">

          <header class="about-header">
            <p class="about-tag">About Yarova</p>
            <h1>An IT placement consultancy for the AI era.</h1>
          </header>

          <div class="about-content">

            <section>
              <p class="intro">
                Yarova is built on a single thesis: the knowledge is real, but the standard format was never built to surface it. We fix the format — with a structured program, real GitHub artifacts, and coaching that runs from study to Day 90.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>What we do</h2>
              <p>
                We get people into DevOps, SRE, and Platform Engineering roles in Canada. Not through shortcuts, not through badges — through genuine depth, built in public, on GitHub, where hiring managers can inspect it.
              </p>
              <p>
                The program is 8 phases, 33 tickets, 3 repositories, and direct coaching from an engineer who has operated production systems at scale. When you finish, you have a GitHub history a hiring manager can open.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>What we believe</h2>
              <div class="values-grid">
                <div class="value">
                  <h3>Depth over breadth</h3>
                  <p>Certifications give you breadth. This program gives you depth. The market for shallow knowledge is overcrowded. The market for depth is not.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value">
                  <h3>Honesty over polish</h3>
                  <p>We tell you what the program won't do as clearly as what it will. No placement guarantee. No hand-holding without effort. That clarity is how trust is built.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value">
                  <h3>Structure over blank pages</h3>
                  <p>A blank document doesn't help when your working memory is full. Every phase has structure. Every ticket has acceptance criteria. You always know what comes next.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="value">
                  <h3>Craft over shortcuts</h3>
                  <p>The program is intense because the work is intense. Every ticket is reviewed. Every deliverable ships to GitHub. The standard is production, not classroom.</p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section>
              <h2>Who runs it</h2>
              <div class="founder-block">
                <div class="founder-info">
                  <h3>Rohith Yadla</h3>
                  <p class="founder-role">Founder &amp; Solutions Architect</p>
                  <p>
                    Yarova is built and run by Rohith Yadla — Solutions Architect with 10 years of production consulting experience across financial systems, enterprise cloud, and public sector infrastructure.
                  </p>
                  <ul class="anchor-list">
                    <li>Morgan Stanley &mdash; financial systems consulting, trading infrastructure at scale</li>
                    <li>Salesforce &mdash; platform engineering consulting, enterprise Kubernetes and cloud</li>
                    <li>BC Government &mdash; Solutions Architect consulting, public sector infrastructure spanning 12+ ministries</li>
                  </ul>
                  <p>
                    On-call rotations. Systems handling money, traffic, and customer data. Real production pressure. The program is built from that experience.
                  </p>
                  <div class="founder-links">
                    <a href="https://github.com/yarova-ca" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>
                    <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/rohithyadla" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="connect">
              <h2>Talk to us</h2>
              <p>
                The first step is a 30-minute discovery call. We learn where you are, you learn what you're committing to. About a third of applicants get a yes. The rest get a clear path forward.
              </p>
              <a href="mailto:hello@yarova.ca" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Schedule a fit call</a>
            </section>

          </div>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  main {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .about-inner {
    max-width: var(--content-width);
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 0 var(--space-6);
  }

  .about-header {
    padding: var(--space-20) 0 var(--space-8);
  }

  .about-tag {
    font-size: var(--text-xs);
    font-weight: 700;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--color-amber);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .about-header h1 {
    font-size: var(--text-4xl);
    letter-spacing: -0.03em;
    line-height: 1.2;
  }

  .about-content section {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-12);
    padding-bottom: var(--space-12);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .about-content section:last-child {
    border-bottom: none;
  }

  .about-content h2 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-content p {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .about-content p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  .intro {
    font-size: var(--text-lg) !important;
    color: var(--text-primary) !important;
  }

  .values-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fill, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-5);
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .value {
    padding: var(--space-6);
    background: var(--bg-secondary);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
  }

  .value h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-base);
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-amber);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-3);
  }

  .value p {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    margin: 0;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  .founder-block {
    margin-top: var(--space-6);
  }

  .founder-info h3 {
    font-size: var(--text-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-1);
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .founder-role {
    font-size: var(--text-sm) !important;
    color: var(--color-amber) !important;
    font-weight: 500;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5) !important;
  }

  .anchor-list {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin: var(--space-5) 0;
  }

  .anchor-list li {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    line-height: 1.65;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
    padding-left: var(--space-4);
    position: relative;
  }

  .anchor-list li::before {
    content: '·';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--color-amber);
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .founder-links {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    margin-top: var(--space-5);
  }

  .founder-links a {
    font-size: var(--text-sm);
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--color-amber);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--transition-fast);
  }

  .founder-links a:hover {
    color: var(--color-amber-hover);
  }

  .connect .btn {
    text-decoration: none;
    margin-top: var(--space-2);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .about-header {
      padding: var(--space-12) 0 var(--space-6);
    }

    .about-header h1 {
      font-size: var(--text-3xl);
    }

    .values-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
